---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import MascotTip from '../../components/MascotTip.astro';
import AuthorByline from '../../components/AuthorByline.astro';
import EmailCapture from '../../components/EmailCapture.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Costco Stack: How I Earn 6% on $10K/Year in Groceries"
  description="Executive membership + Costco Anywhere Visa = 6% total return. Plus a potential rent day hack that could push it even higher. Here's the math."
>
  <article style="max-width: 48rem; margin: 0 auto; padding: 8rem 0 4rem;">
    <h1 style="font-size: 3rem; font-weight: 900; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--color-text); line-height: 1.1;">
      The Costco Stack: How I Earn 6% on $10K/Year in Groceries
    </h1>

    <p style="font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: 2rem; line-height: 1.7;">
      Executive membership + Costco Visa + a potential BILT hack = ridiculous returns
    </p>

    <AuthorByline date="March 16, 2026" />

    <div style="font-size: 1.125rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-text-muted);">
      
      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        Costco is the biggest grocery spend for most households. For me, it's easily $10K/year—probably more. If you're going to spend that much money anyway, you might as well optimize the return.
      </p>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        Here's how I stack Costco Executive membership with the Costco Anywhere Visa to earn 6% on everything I buy there. And a potential hack that could push it even higher.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text);">
        The Two-Card Stack
      </h2>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        There are two pieces to this strategy:
      </p>

      <ul style="margin: 2rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;">
        <li><strong>Costco Executive Membership</strong> ($130/year, 2% annual rebate)</li>
        <li><strong>Costco Anywhere Visa</strong> (no annual fee, 4% gas + 2% Costco purchases)</li>
      </ul>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        The Executive membership gives you 2% back on everything you buy at Costco, paid out once a year as a check. The Visa gives you an additional 2% back on Costco purchases, plus 4% on gas.
      </p>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        Stack them together, and you're earning <strong>4% on all Costco purchases</strong>. But there's more.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text);">
        The Gas Arbitrage
      </h2>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        I live in a high cost-of-living area. Gas is expensive. Costco consistently has the cheapest prices—usually 20-30¢/gallon lower than nearby stations.
      </p>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        When you combine the price discount with 4% cashback from the Visa card, you're saving 50-60¢/gallon compared to paying full price at a Shell station.
      </p>

      <div style="background-color: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0;">
        <h4 style="font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--color-text);">Gas Savings Example</h4>
        <div style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 2;">
          <div>Shell price: $4.50/gal</div>
          <div>Costco price: $4.20/gal</div>
          <div>4% cashback: -$0.17/gal</div>
          <div style="margin-top: 0.5rem; padding-top: 0.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); font-weight: 700;">
            Effective price: $4.03/gal
          </div>
          <div style="margin-top: 0.5rem; color: var(--color-success); font-weight: 700;">
            Savings: $0.47/gal (10.4%)
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        If you drive regularly, the gas savings alone can pay for the Executive membership.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text);">
        The In-Store Math
      </h2>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        Groceries are the real play. Most households spend $500-1,000/month at Costco. At the low end, that's $6K/year. At the high end, it's $12K+.
      </p>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        With the Executive + Visa stack, you're earning 4% on all of it.
      </p>

      <div style="background-color: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0;">
        <h4 style="font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--color-text);">Annual Return Example</h4>
        <div style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 2;">
          <div><strong>Scenario 1: $6K/year spend</strong></div>
          <div style="margin-left: 1rem;">Executive rebate (2%): $120</div>
          <div style="margin-left: 1rem;">Visa cashback (2%): $120</div>
          <div style="margin-left: 1rem; padding-top: 0.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); font-weight: 700;">
            Total return: $240
          </div>
          <div style="margin-left: 1rem;">Minus membership: -$130</div>
          <div style="margin-left: 1rem; padding-top: 0.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-success);">
            Net gain: $110
          </div>

          <div style="margin-top: 1.5rem;"><strong>Scenario 2: $10K/year spend</strong></div>
          <div style="margin-left: 1rem;">Executive rebate (2%): $200</div>
          <div style="margin-left: 1rem;">Visa cashback (2%): $200</div>
          <div style="margin-left: 1rem; padding-top: 0.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); font-weight: 700;">
            Total return: $400
          </div>
          <div style="margin-left: 1rem;">Minus membership: -$130</div>
          <div style="margin-left: 1rem; padding-top: 0.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-success);">
            Net gain: $270
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        At $10K/year in Costco spend (which is very achievable for a household), you're netting $270 after the membership fee. That's a 2.7% effective return even after paying for the upgrade.
      </p>

      <MascotTip type="tip">
        <p><strong>Break-even point:</strong> You need to spend $3,250/year at Costco for the Executive membership to pay for itself with the rebate alone. Add the Visa cashback, and the break-even drops to $1,625.</p>
      </MascotTip>

      <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text);">
        The BILT Rent Day Hack (Unverified But Promising)
      </h2>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        Here's a potential play I've heard about but haven't fully tested yet: buying Costco shop cards with your BILT Palladium on rent day.
      </p>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        If you buy $500 worth of Costco shop cards on the 1st of the month, you'd earn:
      </p>

      <ul style="margin: 2rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;">
        <li>4x BILT points (4% on rent day, points double)</li>
        <li>4% BILT cash (does NOT double on rent day)</li>
      </ul>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        That's 8% back on the shop card purchase. Then, when you use the shop cards at Costco:
      </p>

      <ul style="margin: 2rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;">
        <li>2% Executive rebate (maybe—unclear if shop cards qualify)</li>
      </ul>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        If the Executive rebate stacks, you'd be earning 10% total (8% BILT + 2% Executive). If it doesn't, you're still at 8% from the BILT card alone—which is 4x the baseline Costco Visa return.
      </p>

      <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fef3c7 0%, #fde68a 100%); border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; border-radius: var(--radius-md);">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 1rem;">
          <div style="font-size: 1.5rem; flex-shrink: 0;">⚠️</div>
          <div>
            <h4 style="font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1rem;">
              Testing Required
            </h4>
            <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;">
              I haven't verified whether Costco shop card purchases qualify for the Executive rebate. If you test this, let me know the results. If it works, this becomes one of the best plays in the game.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text);">
        Why This Beats Other Grocery Cards
      </h2>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        Most grocery-focused cards offer 3-6% cashback. That sounds great until you factor in annual fees and category caps.
      </p>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        The Costco stack offers:
      </p>

      <ul style="margin: 2rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;">
        <li><strong>No category caps</strong> (earn on unlimited Costco spend)</li>
        <li><strong>Bulk pricing discount</strong> (Costco is already 10-20% cheaper than grocery stores)</li>
        <li><strong>Gas savings</strong> (not included in grocery card math)</li>
        <li><strong>Potential BILT stacking</strong> (if shop card hack works)</li>
      </ul>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        When you combine the Costco bulk discount with the 4% cashback, you're effectively saving 14-24% compared to buying the same products at a regular grocery store with a 3% cashback card.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text);">
        When It Makes Sense (And When It Doesn't)
      </h2>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text);">
        This stack is worth it if:
      </p>

      <ul style="margin: 2rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;">
        <li>You already shop at Costco regularly</li>
        <li>You spend $3,250+/year there (break-even for Executive)</li>
        <li>You drive and can use Costco gas</li>
        <li>You have storage space for bulk purchases</li>
      </ul>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text);">
        Skip it if:
      </p>

      <ul style="margin: 2rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;">
        <li>You don't have a Costco nearby</li>
        <li>You won't spend enough to break even on the membership</li>
        <li>You prefer smaller purchases over bulk buying</li>
        <li>You don't drive (gas savings won't apply)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text);">
        My Estimated Annual Return
      </h2>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        Based on my actual Costco spending (rough estimate, I don't track every receipt):
      </p>

      <div style="background-color: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0;">
        <div style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 2;">
          <div><strong>Costco groceries/household:</strong> ~$10K/year</div>
          <div style="margin-left: 1rem;">Executive rebate (2%): $200</div>
          <div style="margin-left: 1rem;">Visa cashback (2%): $200</div>
          
          <div style="margin-top: 1rem;"><strong>Gas:</strong> ~$2K/year</div>
          <div style="margin-left: 1rem;">Visa cashback (4%): $80</div>
          
          <div style="margin-top: 1rem; padding-top: 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); font-weight: 700;">
            <strong>Total cashback:</strong> $480
          </div>
          <div style="margin-top: 0.5rem;">
            <strong>Minus membership:</strong> -$130
          </div>
          <div style="margin-top: 0.5rem; padding-top: 0.5rem; border-top: 2px solid var(--color-border); font-weight: 900; font-size: 1.125rem; color: var(--color-success);">
            <strong>Net annual return:</strong> $350
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        That's $350 for doing exactly what I was already doing—buying groceries and gas. If the BILT shop card hack works, this number could double.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text);">
        The Bottom Line
      </h2>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        The Costco stack is simple, reliable, and scales with your spending. There's no optimization required beyond using the right cards.
      </p>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        If you're already shopping at Costco, this is free money. If you're not, the combined savings (bulk pricing + cashback + gas) might justify starting.
      </p>

      <p style="margin: 2rem 0;">
        And if the BILT shop card hack works, this becomes one of the highest-returning grocery strategies available.
      </p>

      <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text);">
        Related Strategies
      </h2>

      <ul style="margin: 2rem 0 4rem; padding-left: 0; list-style: none;">
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
          <a href="/strategies/bilt-palladium-deep-dive" style="color: var(--color-secondary); text-decoration: underline; font-weight: 600;">Why I Pay $500/Year for the BILT Palladium Card</a>
        </li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
          <a href="/strategies/rent-day-optimization" style="color: var(--color-secondary); text-decoration: underline; font-weight: 600;">BILT Rent Day: The 4x Multiplier Most People Miss</a>
        </li>
        <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
          <a href="/strategies/secret-sauce" style="color: var(--color-secondary); text-decoration: underline; font-weight: 600;">My Full $3,500+/Year Rewards Strategy</a>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <EmailCapture
        variant="article-end"
        headline="Want the Costco optimization spreadsheet?"
        description="I'll send you my annual tracking sheet that calculates your exact break-even point and potential returns."
        buttonText="Send me the spreadsheet"
      />

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
